Headline::::
Ireland recall Jared Payne to midfield for Six Nations match with Italy




DateTime::::2016-03-10T14:18:27+0000



<p>Joe Schmidt has signalled Ireland’s desperation for victory against Italy on Saturday by restoring the fit-again Jared Payne back into his midfield rather than shifting the Ulsterman to full-back.</p>

<p><a class="u-underline" data-component="in-body-link" data-link-name="in body link" href="http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/mar/21/ireland-win-six-nations-england-fall-short" title="">The 2015 Six Nations champions</a> are still chasing their first win of this year’s tournament at the fourth time of asking, leaving their head coach refusing to take any chances against the Azzurri in Dublin.</p>

<p> <span>Related: </span><a class="u-underline" data-component="in-body-link" data-link-name="in body link" href="http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/mar/02/martin-castrogiovanni-banned-stamp-italy-ireland-scotland-six-nations-rugby">Italy prop Martin Castrogiovanni banned for two weeks for stamping</a> </p>

<p>Rob Kearney has failed to overcome his hamstring strain, leading Schmidt to slot Simon Zebo into the full-back place. Schmidt could have shifted the 30-year-old Payne to the 15 shirt to allow Ulster’s Stuart McCloskey to continue at inside centre. However, the coach has resisted the temptation to build for the future and has decided against handing McCloskey another opportunity.</p>

<p>McCloskey won his Test debut in Ireland’s <a class="u-underline" data-component="in-body-link" data-link-name="in body link" href="http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2016/feb/27/england-ireland-six-nations-match-report" title="">21-10 defeat by England</a>, forming a bruising midfield partnership with Robbie Henshaw.</p>

<p>Payne missed the Twickenham match with hamstring trouble but has been brought straight back into the No13 role after finding full fitness at the start of the week. Schmidt has long staked much of his Ireland tenure around the New Zealand-born Payne’s defensive stability in midfield, and has duly reverted to type at the first given opportunity.</p>

<p>Leinster’s Josh van der Flier continues at openside flanker with Sean O’Brien ruled out for the tournament.</p>

<p>S Zebo (Munster); A Trimble, J Payne (both Ulster), R Henshaw (Connacht), K Earls (Munster); J Sexton (Leinster), C Murray (Munster); J McGrath (Leinster), R Best (Ulster, capt), M Ross (Leinster), D Ryan (Munster) D Toner (Leinster), CJ Stander (Munster), J Van der Flier, J Heaslip (both Leinster).</p>




